Version: {{ VER }}
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Gabriel Guillou guillou.gabriel@gmail.com
Homepage: https://github.com/DaemonCores/DaemonCores-VE
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Depends: libcomposefs, libostree, util-linux, coreutils, {{ DEPS }}
Description: run bootc/OCI images as unprivileged, immutable Proxmox LXC
 Deploys a bootc (OCI) image on the host as an ostree/composefs deployment and
 presents it as the rootfs of a standard, unprivileged Proxmox container.
 .
 The rootfs is the composefs view of the deployment, id-shifted at mount time
 with `mount.composefs -o idmap=` so the read-only, fs-verity-checked image maps
 to root inside the container without any chown or overlay idmapped-mount. /usr
 stays immutable; /etc and /var are writable per-container layers attached as
 ordinary PVE mount points. Containers are unprivileged with nesting enabled —
 the posture of a normal PVE systemd guest, no extra privilege.
 .
 Image updates are atomic and roll back: a new revision is deployed and the
 container restarts onto it, while the previous deployment is kept so a bad
 update is undone by restarting onto it rather than mutating a live root. A
 boot-time service re-establishes every managed rootfs before pve-guests starts.
